Code chunks

Here’s a first code chunk using the data set cars that comes in R

summary(cars)
##      speed           dist       
##  Min.   : 4.0   Min.   :  2.00  
##  1st Qu.:12.0   1st Qu.: 26.00  
##  Median :15.0   Median : 36.00  
##  Mean   :15.4   Mean   : 42.98  
##  3rd Qu.:19.0   3rd Qu.: 56.00  
##  Max.   :25.0   Max.   :120.00

More chunks

Here’s another chunk:

# matrix of correlation
cor(cars)
##           speed      dist
## speed 1.0000000 0.8068949
## dist  0.8068949 1.0000000

Plots

Basic Plot

plot(cars)

Fancy Plot

p <- ggplot(data = cars, aes(x = speed, y = dist)) +
  geom_point(col = '#FF7722')

plot_ly(p)

Inline code

You can also include inline code. For example, cars has 50 rows. The average speed is 15.4.

Some Equations

Likewise, it is possible to include equations. We can write a model like this: \[ dist = f(speed) \]
